code: @Transactional public class UserService { private final UserRepository userRepository; private final PasswordEncoder passwordEncoder; public UserService(UserRepository userRepository, PasswordEncoder passwordEncoder) {this.userRepository = userRepository; this.passwordEncoder = passwordEncoder;} public List<UserDto> findAll(){ return userRepository.findAll().stream() .map(this::convertToDto).toList(); } public UserDto findUserById(int userId){ User user = userRepository.findById(userId) .orElseThrow(() -> new UserNotFoundException(userId)); return convertToDto(user); } public User registerUser(UserDto userDto){ User user = new User( userDto.firstName(), userDto.lastName(), userDto.email(), userDto.isLecturer(), userDto.address(), userDto.phoneNumber(), passwordEncoder.encode(userDto.password()) ); return userRepository.save(user); } public User makeLecturer(int userId){ User user = userRepository.findById(userId) .orElseThrow(() -> new UserNotFoundException(userId)); user.setLecturer(true); return userRepository.save(user); } public UserDto convertToDto(User user){ return new UserDto( user.getFirstName(), user.getLastName(), user.getEmail(), user.isLecturer(), user.getAddress(), user.getPhoneNumber(), "" ); } public List<WebinarDto> getUserWebinars(int userId){ User user = userRepository.findById(userId) .orElseThrow(() -> new UserNotFoundException(userId)); Set<Webinar> webinars = user.getWebinars(); List<WebinarDto> webinarDtos = new ArrayList<>(); for(Webinar webinar : webinars){ webinarDtos.add(convertToDto(webinar)); } return webinarDtos; } private WebinarDto convertToDto(Webinar webinar){ Address address = webinar.getClassroom().getAddress(); ClassroomDto classroomDto = new ClassroomDto(webinar.getClassroom().getClassroomId(), new ClassroomAddressDto(address.getCity(), address.getStreet(), address.getNumber()), webinar.getClassroom().getCapacity(), webinar.getClassroom().getRoomNumber()); User lecturer = webinar.getLecturer(); UserDto lecturerDto = new UserDto(lecturer.getFirstName(), lecturer.getLastName(), lecturer.getEmail(), lecturer.isLecturer(), lecturer.getAddress(), lecturer.getPhoneNumber(), ""); return new WebinarDto(webinar.getWebinarId(),webinar.getWebinarName(), webinar.getDateTime(), webinar.getDuration(), lecturerDto, classroomDto, webinar.getCategories().stream().map(Category::getName).collect(Collectors.toSet())); } }

label: ClassroomService
code: @Transactional public class ClassroomService { private final ClassroomRepository classroomRepository; public ClassroomService(ClassroomRepository classroomRepository) { this.classroomRepository = classroomRepository; } public List<ClassroomDto> findAll() { return classroomRepository.findAll().stream() .map(this::convertToDto) .toList(); } public ClassroomDto getClassroomById(int id) { Classroom classroom = classroomRepository.findById(id) .orElseThrow(() -> new ClassroomNotFoundException(id)); return convertToDto(classroom); } public List<ClassroomDto> getClassroomsByAddress(ClassroomAddressDto addressDto) { Address address = new Address( addressDto.city(), addressDto.street(), addressDto.number() ); List<Classroom> classrooms = classroomRepository.findByAddress(address); return classrooms.stream() .map(this::convertToDto) .toList(); } public ClassroomDto createClassroom(ClassroomDto classroomDto) { Address address = new Address( classroomDto.address().city(), classroomDto.address().street(), classroomDto.address().number() ); Optional<Classroom> existingClassroom = classroomRepository .findByAddressAndRoomNumber(address, classroomDto.roomNumber()); if (existingClassroom.isPresent()) { throw new ClassroomAlreadyExsistsException( classroomDto.address().city(), classroomDto.address().street(), classroomDto.address().number(), classroomDto.roomNumber() ); } Classroom classroom = new Classroom( address, classroomDto.roomNumber(), classroomDto.capacity() ); return convertToDto(classroomRepository.save(classroom)); } public ClassroomDto updateClassroom(int id, ClassroomDto classroomDto) { Classroom classroom = classroomRepository.findById(id) .orElseThrow(() -> new ClassroomNotFoundException(id)); Address newAddress = new Address( classroomDto.address().city(), classroomDto.address().street(), classroomDto.address().number() ); classroom.setAddress(newAddress); classroom.setRoomNumber(classroomDto.roomNumber()); classroom.setCapacity(classroomDto.capacity()); return convertToDto(classroomRepository.save(classroom)); } public void deleteClassroom(int id) { Classroom classroom = classroomRepository.findById(id) .orElseThrow(() -> new ClassroomNotFoundException(id)); if(!classroom.getWebinars().isEmpty()){ throw new ClassroomInUseException(id); } classroomRepository.deleteById(id); } public ClassroomDto convertToDto(Classroom classroom) { Address address = classroom.getAddress(); ClassroomAddressDto addressDto = new ClassroomAddressDto( address.getCity(), address.getStreet(), address.getNumber() ); return new ClassroomDto( classroom.getClassroomId(), addressDto, classroom.getCapacity(), classroom.getRoomNumber() ); } }

label: Webinar
code: @Entity public class Webinar { @Id @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY) private int webinarId; private String webinarName; private LocalDateTime dateTime; @Convert(converter = DurationConverter.class) private Duration duration; @ManyToOne private User lecturer; @ManyToOne private Classroom classroom; @ManyToMany private Set<User> students = new HashSet<>(); @ManyToMany private Set<Category> categories = new HashSet<>(); private int maxCapacity; public Webinar(String webinarName, LocalDateTime dateTime, Duration duration, User lecturer, Classroom classroom, int maxCapacity) { this.webinarName = webinarName; this.dateTime = dateTime; this.duration = duration; this.lecturer = lecturer; this.classroom = classroom; this.maxCapacity = maxCapacity; } public Webinar() { } public String getWebinarName() { return webinarName; } public int getWebinarId() { return webinarId; } public LocalDateTime getDateTime() { return dateTime; } public Duration getDuration() { return duration; } public User getLecturer() { return lecturer; } public Classroom getClassroom() { return classroom; } public Set<User> getStudents() { return students; } public Set<Category> getCategories() { return categories; } public int getMaxCapacity() { return maxCapacity; } public void enrollStudent(User student) { students.add(student); student.enroll(this); } public void unenrollStudent(User student) { if (students.contains(student)) { students.remove(student); student.unenroll(this); } else { throw new IllegalStateException("User is not enrolled in this webinar."); } } public void setWebinarName(String webinarName) { this.webinarName = webinarName; } public void setDateTime(LocalDateTime dateTime) { this.dateTime = dateTime; } public void setDuration(Duration duration) { this.duration = duration; } public void setLecturer(User lecturer) { this.lecturer = lecturer; } public void setClassroom(Classroom classroom) { this.classroom = classroom; } public void setMaxCapacity(int maxCapacity) { this.maxCapacity = maxCapacity; } public void addCategory(Category category) { this.categories.add(category); } public void removeCategory(Category category) { this.categories.remove(category); } }

label: WebinarService
code: @Transactional public class WebinarService { private final WebinarRepository webinarRepository; private final UserService userService; private final UserRepository userRepository; private final ClassroomRepository classroomRepository; private final CategoryRepository categoryRepository; public WebinarService(WebinarRepository webinarRepository, UserService userService, UserRepository userRepository, ClassroomRepository classroomRepository, CategoryRepository categoryRepository) { this.webinarRepository = webinarRepository; this.userService = userService; this.userRepository = userRepository; this.classroomRepository = classroomRepository; this.categoryRepository = categoryRepository; } public WebinarDto getWebinarById(int id) { Webinar webinar = webinarRepository.findById(id).orElseThrow(() -> new WebinarNotFoundException(id)); return convertToDto(webinar); } public WebinarDto addWebinar(WebinarDto webinarDto) { if (webinarDto.webinarDate().isBefore(LocalDateTime.now())) { throw new IllegalArgumentException("Webinar date cannot be in the past."); } if (webinarDto.webinarDate().isAfter(LocalDateTime.now().plusYears(2))) { throw new IllegalArgumentException("Webinar date cannot be set 2 years in the future."); } User lecturer = userRepository.findByEmail(webinarDto.lecturer().email()) .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Lecturer not found")); Classroom classroom = classroomRepository.findById(webinarDto.classroom().classroomId()) .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Classroom not found")); Webinar webinar = new Webinar( webinarDto.webinarName(), webinarDto.webinarDate(), webinarDto.duration(), lecturer, classroom, webinarDto.classroom().capacity() ); // Convert category names to Category entities Set<Category> categories = webinarDto.categories().stream() .map(categoryName -> categoryRepository.findByName(categoryName) .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Category not found: " + categoryName))) .collect(Collectors.toSet()); webinar.getCategories().addAll(categories); Set<Webinar> overlappingWebinars = overlappingWebinarsForUser(lecturer, webinar); if (!overlappingWebinars.isEmpty()) { String overlappingDetails = overlappingWebinars.stream() .map(w -> w.getWebinarId() + "." + w.getWebinarName() + " (" + w.getDateTime() + ")") .collect(Collectors.joining(", ")); throw new WebinarOverlappingException(lecturer.getUserId(), webinar.getWebinarId(), overlappingDetails); } Webinar savedWebinar = webinarRepository.save(webinar); return convertToDto(savedWebinar); } public List<WebinarDto> getWebinarsByDateRange(LocalDateTime from, LocalDateTime to){ return webinarRepository.findByDateTimeBetween(from, to).stream() .map(this::convertToDto).toList(); } public List<WebinarDto> getWebinarsByCategory(String categoryName) { return webinarRepository.findAll().stream() .filter(webinar -> webinar.getCategories().stream() .anyMatch(category -> category.getName().equalsIgnoreCase(categoryName))) .map(this::convertToDto) .toList(); } public List<WebinarDto> getWebinarsByLecturer(String firstName, String lastName) { return webinarRepository.findAll().stream() .filter(webinar -> webinar.getLecturer() != null && webinar.getLecturer().getFirstName().equalsIgnoreCase(firstName) && webinar.getLecturer().getLastName().equalsIgnoreCase(lastName)) .map(this::convertToDto) .toList(); } public List<WebinarDto> findAll() { return webinarRepository.findAll().stream() .map(this::convertToDto).toList(); } public List<UserDto> getStudentsForWebinar(int webinarId) { Webinar webinar = webinarRepository.findById(webinarId) .orElseThrow(() -> new WebinarNotFoundException(webinarId)); return webinar.getStudents().stream() .map(userService::convertToDto) .toList(); } public WebinarDto updateWebinar(int webinarId, WebinarDto webinarDto) { Classroom classroom; Webinar webinar = webinarRepository.findById(webinarId) .orElseThrow(() -> new WebinarNotFoundException(webinarId)); webinar.setWebinarName(webinarDto.webinarName()); webinar.setDateTime(webinarDto.webinarDate()); webinar.setDuration(webinarDto.duration()); if (webinarDto.lecturer() != null && webinarDto.lecturer().email() != null) { String lecturerEmail = webinarDto.lecturer().email(); User lecturer = userRepository.findByEmail(lecturerEmail) .orElseThrow(() -> new UserNotFoundException(lecturerEmail)); webinar.setLecturer(lecturer); } Address newAddress = new Address(webinarDto.classroom().address().city(), webinarDto.classroom().address().street(), webinarDto.classroom().address().number()); Optional<Classroom> existingClassroom = classroomRepository.findByAddressAndRoomNumber(newAddress, webinarDto.classroom().roomNumber()); if (existingClassroom.isPresent()) { classroom = existingClassroom.get(); } else { throw new ClassroomNotFoundException(newAddress.getCity(), newAddress.getStreet(), newAddress.getNumber(), webinarDto.classroom().roomNumber()); } webinar.setClassroom(classroom); // Update categories Set<Category> categories = webinarDto.categories().stream() .map(categoryName -> categoryRepository.findByName(categoryName) .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Category not found: " + categoryName))) .collect(Collectors.toSet()); webinar.getCategories().clear(); webinar.getCategories().addAll(categories); Webinar updatedWebinar = webinarRepository.save(webinar); return convertToDto(updatedWebinar); } public WebinarDto enrollStudentIntoWebinar(int webinarId, int userId){ Webinar webinar = webinarRepository.findById(webinarId) .orElseThrow(() -> new WebinarNotFoundException(webinarId)); User user = userRepository.findById(userId) .orElseThrow(() -> new UserNotFoundException(userId)); if (webinar.getStudents().contains(user) || user.getWebinars().contains(webinar)) { throw new UserAlreadyEnrolledException(userId, webinarId); } if (user.getEmail().equalsIgnoreCase(webinar.getLecturer().getEmail())) { throw new LecturerCantEnrollIntoOwnWebinar(); } Set<Webinar> overlappingWebinars = overlappingWebinarsForUser(user, webinar); if (!overlappingWebinars.isEmpty()) { String overlappingWebinarsDetails = overlappingWebinars.stream() .map(w -> w.getWebinarId() + "." + w.getWebinarName() + " (" + w.getDateTime() + ")") .collect(Collectors.joining(", ")); throw new WebinarOverlappingException(userId, webinarId, overlappingWebinarsDetails); } webinar.enrollStudent(user); webinarRepository.save(webinar); userRepository.save(user); return convertToDto(webinar); } public WebinarDto unenrollStudentIntoWebinar(int webinarId,int userId){ Webinar webinar = webinarRepository.findById(webinarId) .orElseThrow(() -> new WebinarNotFoundException(webinarId)); User user = userRepository.findById(userId) .orElseThrow(() -> new UserNotFoundException(userId)); if(!webinar.getStudents().contains(user)){ throw new UserNotEnrolledException(user.getFirstName() + " " + user.getLastName(), webinar.getWebinarName()); } webinar.unenrollStudent(user); webinarRepository.save(webinar); return convertToDto(webinar); } public void deleteWebinar(int webinarId) { webinarRepository.findById(webinarId) .orElseThrow(() -> new WebinarNotFoundException(webinarId)); webinarRepository.deleteById(webinarId); } public List<WebinarDto> getFutureWebinars() { LocalDateTime currentDateTime = LocalDateTime.now(); List<WebinarDto> allWebinars = findAll(); return allWebinars .stream().filter(webinar -> webinar.webinarDate().isAfter(currentDateTime)) .collect(Collectors.toList()); } public List<WebinarDto> getSortedWebinars(String sortBy, String order) { Sort.Direction direction = Sort.Direction.fromString(order); List<Webinar> sortedWebinars; switch (sortBy.toLowerCase()){ case "date": sortedWebinars = direction == Sort.Direction.ASC ? webinarRepository.findAllByOrderByDateTimeAsc() : webinarRepository.findAllByOrderByDateTimeDesc(); break; case "classroom": sortedWebinars = direction == Sort.Direction.ASC ? webinarRepository.findAllByOrderByClassroomAsc() : webinarRepository.findAllByOrderByClassroomDesc(); break; case "name": sortedWebinars = direction == Sort.Direction.ASC ? webinarRepository.findAllByOrderByWebinarNameAsc() : webinarRepository.findAllByOrderByWebinarNameDesc(); break; default: throw new InvalidSortByParamException(sortBy); } return sortedWebinars .stream() .map(this::convertToDto) .toList(); } private WebinarDto convertToDto(Webinar webinar){ Address address = webinar.getClassroom().getAddress(); ClassroomDto classroomDto = new ClassroomDto(webinar.getClassroom().getClassroomId(), new ClassroomAddressDto(address.getCity(), address.getStreet(), address.getNumber()), webinar.getClassroom().getCapacity(), webinar.getClassroom().getRoomNumber()); User lecturer = webinar.getLecturer(); UserDto lecturerDto = new UserDto(lecturer.getFirstName(), lecturer.getLastName(), lecturer.getEmail(), lecturer.isLecturer(), lecturer.getAddress(), lecturer.getPhoneNumber(), ""); return new WebinarDto(webinar.getWebinarId(),webinar.getWebinarName(), webinar.getDateTime(), webinar.getDuration(), lecturerDto, classroomDto, webinar.getCategories().stream().map(Category::getName).collect(Collectors.toSet())); } public Set<Webinar> overlappingWebinarsForUser(User user, Webinar newWebinar) { LocalDateTime newWebinarStart = newWebinar.getDateTime(); LocalDateTime newWebinarEnd = newWebinar.getDateTime().plusMinutes(newWebinar.getDuration().toMinutes()); Set<Webinar> overlappingWebinars = new HashSet<>(); Set<Webinar> userWebinars = user.getWebinars(); for (Webinar webinar : userWebinars) { LocalDateTime oldWebinarStart = webinar.getDateTime(); LocalDateTime oldWebinarEnd = webinar.getDateTime().plusMinutes(webinar.getDuration().toMinutes()); if (isOverlapping(newWebinarStart, newWebinarEnd, oldWebinarStart, oldWebinarEnd)) { overlappingWebinars.add(webinar); } } return overlappingWebinars; } private boolean isOverlapping(LocalDateTime start1, LocalDateTime end1, LocalDateTime start2, LocalDateTime end2) { return start1.isBefore(end2) && start2.isBefore(end1); } }

label: CategoryService
code: @Transactional public class CategoryService { private final CategoryRepository categoryRepository; public CategoryService(CategoryRepository categoryRepository) { this.categoryRepository = categoryRepository; } public List<CategoryDto> findAll() { return categoryRepository.findAll().stream() .map(this::convertToDto).toList(); } public CategoryDto getCategoryById(int id) { Category category = categoryRepository.findById(id) .orElseThrow(() -> new CategoryNotFoundException(id)); return convertToDto(category); } public CategoryDto getCategoryByName(String name) { Category category = categoryRepository.findByName(name) .orElseThrow(() -> new CategoryNotFoundException(name)); return convertToDto(category); } public List<CategoryDto> searchCategories(String nameFragment) { return categoryRepository.findByNameContainingIgnoreCase(nameFragment) .stream() .map(this::convertToDto) .toList(); } public CategoryDto createCategory(CategoryDto categoryDto) { if (categoryRepository.existsByName(categoryDto.name())) { throw new CategoryAlreadyExistsException(categoryDto.name()); } Category category = new Category(categoryDto.name()); Category savedCategory = categoryRepository.save(category); return convertToDto(savedCategory); } public CategoryDto updateCategory(int id, CategoryDto categoryDto) { Category category = categoryRepository.findById(id) .orElseThrow(() -> new CategoryNotFoundException(id)); if (!category.getName().equals(categoryDto.name()) && categoryRepository.existsByName(categoryDto.name())) { throw new CategoryAlreadyExistsException(categoryDto.name()); } category.setName(categoryDto.name()); Category updatedCategory = categoryRepository.save(category); return convertToDto(updatedCategory); } public void deleteCategory(int id) { Category category = categoryRepository.findById(id) .orElseThrow(() -> new CategoryNotFoundException(id)); if(!category.getWebinars().isEmpty()){ throw new CategoryInUseException(category.getName()); } categoryRepository.deleteById(id); } private CategoryDto convertToDto(Category category) { return new CategoryDto(category.getCategoryId(), category.getName()); } }

code: @RequestMapping("/login") public class LoginController { private final AuthenticationManager authenticationManager; private final UserRepository userRepository; private final PasswordEncoder passwordEncoder; public LoginController(AuthenticationManager authenticationManager, UserRepository userRepository, PasswordEncoder passwordEncoder) { this.authenticationManager = authenticationManager; this.userRepository = userRepository; this.passwordEncoder = passwordEncoder; } @PostMapping public ResponseEntity<LoginResponse> login(@RequestBody LoginRequest loginRequest) { try { Authentication authentication = authenticationManager.authenticate( new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken( loginRequest.getUsername(), loginRequest.getPassword() ) ); SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication(authentication); String role = authentication.getAuthorities().stream() .findFirst() .map(GrantedAuthority::getAuthority) .orElse("") .replace("ROLE_", ""); com.to.proj.User.User user = userRepository.findByEmail(loginRequest.getUsername()) .orElseThrow(() -> new UsernameNotFoundException("User not found")); return ResponseEntity.ok(new LoginResponse(true, role, user.getUserId())); } catch (AuthenticationException e) { return ResponseEntity.ok(new LoginResponse(false, "", 0)); } } public static class LoginRequest { private String username; private String password; public String getUsername() { return username; } public void setUsername(String username) { this.username = username; } public String getPassword() { return password; } public void setPassword(String password) { this.password = password; } } public static class LoginResponse { private boolean success; private String role; private int userId; public LoginResponse(boolean success, String role, int userId) { this.success = success; this.role = role; this.userId = userId; } public boolean isSuccess() { return success; } public void setSuccess(boolean success) { this.success = success; } public String getRole() { return role; } public void setRole(String role) { this.role = role; } public int getUserId() { return userId; } public void setUserId(int userId) { this.userId = userId; } } }

} @PostMapping public ResponseEntity<WebinarDto> createWebinar(@RequestBody WebinarDto webinarDto) { WebinarDto createdWebinarDto = webinarService.addWebinar(webinarDto); return ResponseEntity.created(URI.create("/webinars/" + createdWebinarDto.id())) .body(createdWebinarDto); } @GetMapping("/{id}/students") public ResponseEntity<List<UserDto>> getStudentsForWebinar(@PathVariable int id) { return ResponseEntity.ok(webinarService.getStudentsForWebinar(id)); } @GetMapping("/by-date-range") public ResponseEntity<?> getWebinarsByDateRange( @RequestParam("fromDate") String fromDate, @RequestParam("toDate") String toDate){ LocalDateTime from = LocalDateTime.parse(fromDate); LocalDateTime to = LocalDateTime.parse(toDate); if (from.isAfter(to)) { Map<String, String> errorResponse = new HashMap<>(); errorResponse.put("error", "fromDate must be earlier than toDate"); return ResponseEntity.badRequest().body(errorResponse); } List<WebinarDto> webinars = webinarService.getWebinarsByDateRange(from,to); return ResponseEntity.ok(webinars); } @PostMapping("/{id}/enroll") public ResponseEntity<WebinarDto> enrollStudentIntoWebinar(@PathVariable int id, @RequestParam int userId){ WebinarDto updatedwebinarDto = webinarService.enrollStudentIntoWebinar(id,userId); return ResponseEntity.ok(updatedwebinarDto); } @DeleteMapping("/{id}/unenroll") public ResponseEntity<WebinarDto> unenrollStudentFromWebinar(@PathVariable int id, @RequestParam int userId){ WebinarDto updatedWebinarDto = webinarService.unenrollStudentIntoWebinar(id, userId); return ResponseEntity.ok(updatedWebinarDto); } @PutMapping("/{id}") public ResponseEntity<WebinarDto> updateWebinar(@PathVariable int id, @RequestBody WebinarDto webinarDto) { WebinarDto updatedWebinar = webinarService.updateWebinar(id, webinarDto); System.out.println(updatedWebinar); return ResponseEntity.ok(updatedWebinar); } @DeleteMapping("/{id}") public ResponseEntity<Void> deleteWebinar(@PathVariable int id) { webinarService.deleteWebinar(id); return ResponseEntity.accepted().build(); } @GetMapping("/category/{categoryName}") public ResponseEntity<List<WebinarDto>> getWebinarsByCategory(@PathVariable String categoryName) { List<WebinarDto> webinars = webinarService.getWebinarsByCategory(categoryName); return ResponseEntity.ok(webinars); } @GetMapping("/by-lecturer") public ResponseEntity<List<WebinarDto>> getWebinarsByLecturer( @RequestParam("firstName") String firstName, @RequestParam("lastName") String lastName) { List<WebinarDto> result = webinarService.getWebinarsByLecturer(firstName, lastName); return ResponseEntity.ok(result); } @GetMapping("/futurewebinars") public ResponseEntity<List<WebinarDto>> getFutureWebinars() { List<WebinarDto> webinars = webinarService.getFutureWebinars(); return ResponseEntity.ok(webinars); } @GetMapping("/sorted-webinars") public ResponseEntity<List<WebinarDto>> getSortedWebinars( @RequestParam String sortBy, @RequestParam(defaultValue = "asc") String order) { List<WebinarDto> sortedWebinars = webinarService.getSortedWebinars(sortBy, order); return ResponseEntity.ok(sortedWebinars); } }

label: User
code: @Table(name = "AppUser") public class User { @Id @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY) private int userId; private String firstName; private String lastName; private String email; private Address address; private String phoneNumber; private boolean isLecturer; @Column(nullable = false) private String password; @ManyToMany(mappedBy = "students") private Set<Webinar> webinars = new HashSet<>(); public User(String firstName, String lastName, String email, boolean isLecturer, Address address, String phoneNumber, String password) { this.firstName = firstName; this.lastName = lastName; this.email = email; this.isLecturer = isLecturer; this.address = address; this.phoneNumber = phoneNumber; this.password = password; } public User(String firstName, String lastName, String email, Address address, String phoneNumber) { this.firstName = firstName; this.lastName = lastName; this.email = email; this.address = address; this.isLecturer = false; this.phoneNumber = phoneNumber; } public User() { } public int getUserId() { return userId; } public String getFirstName() { return firstName; } public String getEmail() { return email; } public String getLastName() { return lastName; } public Address getAddress() { return address; } public boolean isLecturer() { return isLecturer; } public String getPhoneNumber() { return phoneNumber; } public void setLecturer(boolean lecturer) { isLecturer = lecturer; } public Set<Webinar> getWebinars() { return webinars; } public String getPassword() { return password; } public void setPassword(String password) { this.password = password; } public void enroll(Webinar webinar) { webinars.add(webinar); } public void unenroll(Webinar webinar) { webinars.remove(webinar); } }
